commit.message:
Convert iterable to list to reuse in Python 3.

Fixes #48.
Add python3.7 support and remove desupported 3.3 support.

ci: Update .travis.yml to run on Xenial.

This makes it possible to do CI with Python 3.7.
Drop support for EOL Python versions.

Fix fixup_pth_file with files written in UNICODE rather than UTF-8.

This fixes the problem where the converted PTH file was written as
UNICODE rather than UTF-8, complete with a test.

Fix use of .format() so that Python 2.6 works.

Thanks to Jens Anderson for the suggestion.
Modify tox.ini to match Travis CI.

tests: Turn venv_path/clone_path into real paths.

In clonevirtualenv.main we convert paths into real paths. If the real
path is not equal to the oriainal path then tests fail because in
tests/__init__.py the paths defined are not converted to real paths.
testing: Test only available versions of Python.

Use realpath to handle symbolic links.

This fixes the logic to automatically follow symbolic links present in either path passed into the tool.

Match with source venv python version as well.

This takes care of the scheme in which shebang is of type
is of type 3.x e.g. 3.5.

Fixes: #23

Fix invalid regular expression escape sequence in Python 3.

See https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.6.html#deprecated-python-behavior for details.

Merge pull request #17 from marcosdiez/master

Fix symlinks that point to the old virtual env
